# Mision 

## A lightweight fixed-wing UAV optimized for efficient operation across multiple low-speed flight regimes.

# Research question 

## “Can a morphing airfoil improve the aerodynamic efficiency of a low-Reynolds-number UAV across takeoff,
cruise, and landing flight regimes compared to a fixed airfoil configuration?”


# Mission requirements 

The fundamental issue of fixed Airfoils 

| Flight Phase | Desired Airfoil Behaviour | 
|----------|----------|
| Takeoff  | High lift                  | 
| Cruise   | High efficiency            | 
| Landing  | Controlllable near stall   | 

a fixed airfoil cannot be suited for all 3 at the same time as they require fundamentally different properties. 

this is where a morphing wing may be quite useful for us. 

